result.formatted_address: 19 Ormsby St, Tai Hang, Hong Kong
result.name: Yotsuba Cafe

reviews.text:
Tai Hang is one of the hoods I like in Hong Kong. It’s quiet, yet it’s vibrant with so many different types of restaurants and cafes with their own characters and styles.

Yotsuba Cafe is yet another new cafe in Tai Hang. Oh you know, the high turnover rate in Tai Hang due to expensive rent…I decided to try it out before it’s gone too soon.

I was eyeing for the Keto All-Day Breakfast, however, at 5pm I was still a bit full from lunch, so I grabbed this homemade honey scone with a cup of green tea latte.

The homemade scone was amazing even though it didn’t really have a strong honey flavour. It had a crunchy surface and was fluffy inside, that’s what made it up.

The green tea latte was not as good as I thought it would be. It’s too milky and I would like a strong green tea flavour. Maybe the green tea powder they used wasn’t of the top notch? (yes…the drink was very powdery…) The green tea espresso latte might be better? I’m not so sure.
It’s very hard to find a pet friendly cafe in Hong Kong. Thanks to this little cafe. You also find the best Italian coffee - Gaggia. The waffle here is crispy and yummy!

Yotsuba cafe is nicely tucked away in a cozy corner off Ormsby Street in Tai Hang. For us it is like a “living room away from home”. A carefully curated menu promises a delightful visit for breakfast, lunch or tea. My personal favourite is the Keto Breakfast (featuring the owners’ own twist on Ketogenic Diet) and finishing it off with a nice cuppa Gaggia Rose Latte. I had the privilege to sample most of the menu at one go in a private party held recently and all I can say is I can’t wait to drop by again for another visit soon. If only I lived nearer to Yotsuba Cafe.
店外環境相當陳舊，店內播住輕鬆音樂，一個高質獨食餐本來值5星。不過好大冷氣，店內亦只有一張正常餐枱，其餘都要坐bar枱，唔算太舒適，但如果快食，佢又太慢，所以減1星啦！
這𥚃窩夫十分好味，外脆內軟，原來是用日本蛋做的，十分講究！
